---
import LabLayout from '../layouts/LabLayout.astro';
---
<LabLayout
  title="Accessibility Statement — ParlayLab"
  description="Accessibility statement for ParlayLab. We aim to conform to WCAG 2.1 Level AA."
>
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <p class="eyebrow">Accessibility</p>
    <h1 class="display text-4xl sm:text-5xl mt-2">Accessibility Statement</h1>

    <p class="mt-6 text-lab-slate leading-relaxed">
      ParlayLab is built with accessibility as a first-class concern. We use semantic landmarks,
      a visible skip-to-content link, keyboard-reachable navigation, ARIA labels on icon controls,
      and a focus ring that meets contrast requirements. Numeric data uses tabular figures for predictable scanning.
    </p>

    <h2 class="display text-2xl mt-10">Conformance status</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-lab-slate">This site targets <strong>WCAG 2.1 Level AA</strong>. We audit pages with axe-core in development.</p>

    <h2 class="display text-2xl mt-10">Feedback</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-lab-slate">
      Contact us at <a class="text-lab-violet underline" href="mailto:dcraderdev@gmail.com">dcraderdev@gmail.com</a>.
    </p>

    <p class="mt-10 text-lab-mute text-sm"><em>Last updated: 2026-05-17</em></p>
  </section>
</LabLayout>
